sys.argv is the list of commandline arguments passed to the Python program. argv represents all the items that come along via the 
command line input, it's basically an array holding the command line arguments of our program. Don't forget that the counting starts 
at zero (0) not one (1)


import sys
lst=sys.argv
for i in lst:print(i)
print(len(lst))
print(lst[0])

### product of 2 command line arguments

import sys
lst=sys.argv
print("product is",int(lst[1])*int(lst[2]))
